cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with face recognition and proposes a method to improve recognition in the presence of occlusions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a generative model for face completion, which falls under the category of generative models and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the impact of occlusions on recognition, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses 3D rendering techniques, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of biometric systems, which is related to the field of computer security (cs.CR).
